Blocks.Text: He salated, and left the presence, very crestfallen
Time passed. The bus climbed, and went quietly
into orbit. Time passed. The Rev. Edwards pupit
remained empty. And so did the arms of Dai
Pagh. How could they be otherwise, when his
beloved was circling the Poles at three - and -a-
quarter - hour intervals, regular as clockwork?
Time passed. Everyone said, "Pity about Megan
Thomas, isn't it," 11 as though they didn't really think
it was a pity at alli as, indeed, they didn't.
